.TH PICIRE 1 "2026-06-20" "picire 21.8" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
picire \- parallel Delta Debugging framework / automatic test-case reducer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B picire
.B \-i
.I FILE
.B \-\-test
.I FILE
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B picire
is a Python implementation of the (parallel) Delta Debugging algorithm. Given a
failing input file and a test command that reports whether a candidate input is
still "interesting" (for example, still triggers a crash), picire repeatedly
removes parts of the input and keeps the smallest variant that remains
interesting, yielding a minimal reproducer.
.PP
It is language-agnostic \(em it reduces any line- or character-delimited input
\(em and complements the C/C++-aware reducers
.BR cvise (1)
and
.BR creduce (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-input " \fIFILE\fR"
Test case to be reduced.
.TP
.BI \-\-test " FILE"
Test command that decides the interestingness of an input.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-out " \fIDIR\fR"
Working directory (default: input.timestamp).
.TP
.BI \-\-atom " NAME"
Atom (granularity) of the input: char, line, or both (default: line).
.TP
.BI \-\-cache " NAME"
Cache strategy: config, content, or none (default: config).
.TP
.BI \-\-split " NAME"
Split algorithm: balanced or zeller (default: zeller).
.TP
.BI \-\-granularity " N"
Initial granularity and split factor (integer or 'inf'; default: 2).
.TP
.BI \-\-encoding " NAME"
Test-case encoding (default: autodetect).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-parallel
Run Delta Debugging in parallel.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-combine\-loops
Combine subset and complement check loops for more parallelization
(parallel mode only).
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-jobs " \fIN\fR"
Maximum number of test commands to run in parallel (parallel mode only;
default: number of CPUs).
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-max\-utilization " \fIN\fR"
Maximum CPU utilization allowed before starting new parallel jobs
(parallel mode only; default: 100).
.TP
.B \-\-complement\-first
Check complements before subsets.
.TP
.BI \-\-subset\-iterator " NAME"
Subset ordering: backward, forward, random, or skip (default: forward).
.TP
.BI \-\-complement\-iterator " NAME"
Complement ordering: backward, forward, random, or skip (default: forward).
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-log\-level " \fILEVEL\fR"
Diagnostic verbosity: TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL, or DISABLE
(default: INFO).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose mode (alias for \-\-log\-level DEBUG).
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Quiet mode (alias for \-\-log\-level DISABLE).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cleanup
Keep generated temporary files.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show the program's version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLE
Reduce
.I crash.c
to the smallest file for which
.I ./is\-interesting.sh
still exits successfully, using all CPUs:
.PP
.RS
.nf
picire \-\-input crash.c \-\-test ./is\-interesting.sh \-\-parallel
.fi
.RE
